cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel adversarial learning method for unsupervised domain adaptation using deep networks. The paper also involves experiments on benchmark datasets to evaluate the efficacy of the proposed method, which is a common practice in the field of machine learning. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image classification tasks, and natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves text classification tasks. 

The paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of deep neural networks for learning domain-invariant features.
